<br>
Bash, Kick, Taunt, Range (Arrows or Throw, your choice) are the obvious choice.<br>
<br>
An incoming message is a must for pullers. Another  &quot;at-camp&quot; message is also important for lvl 1-35. (The casters have their their faces in the book. After that it loses its importance as the casters can see when the mobs are at camp.)<br>
<br>
Example of inc message &quot;Hey, Target stole my chocolate! Whamp it!&quot;<br>
<br>
Example of At-camp message &quot;Target is at camp!&quot; Useful for alerting the face-in-book casters when the mobs are at camp. Also useful for when a roamer walks toward the camp spot.<br>
<br>
Assist button is a MUST. My assist hot key has the following commands:<br>
1) /g Assisting Target!<br>
2) /assist<br>
<br>
During combat, click on the group member's name (or click on him) and then click on the assist button. Very helpful if you need to assist someone else other than the main assist.<br>
<br>
During the raids or if assisting someone outside the group, change the 1) command line to read, &quot;/tar &lt;name&gt;&quot; It will target that person if within range and you will /assist.<br>
<br>
Lastly, you should have a train message for in case things go bad. The command line should read, &quot;/shout Train to zone... Move it or lose it!&quot;<br>
<br>
Those are the basics you'll need to know. I have many more hot keys, but they're mainly for high-level concepts. (Evac, disciples, etc....)<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
Fibby Stormsong<br>
52 Ogre Champion<br>
